power in north korea my guess is like this they will keep the kim family as a social and political institution like the emperor system in japan offering symbolic and moral power for north koreans but are likely to establish a collective leadership system in which the military will play a key role we may then witness some political instability in the north nytimes north korean leader had surgery after stroke south koreans say search aparc search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest responding to north korea gi wook shin comments in korean media chosun ilbo and hangkook ilbo in korean on may 25 2010 south korean president lee's first 100 days have seen little movement towards narrowing the divide between korea's left and right says center's director gi wook shin ksp in the news korea times on june 24 2008 center's director gi wook shin discusses lee myung bak's win in recent korean presidential election on npr's on the point ksp in the news to the point kcrw national public radio on december 19 2007 prof gi wook shin discussed prospects of korea after its december presidential election november 29 2007 ksp in the news gi wook shin discusses us south korean relations on npr's morning edition june 15 2005 ksp news gi wook shin appointed to be new center director for three year term april 19 2005 ksp news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 9741 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
